reviewText: Shot in ten days with a single hand held camera.The title notwithstanding, that single sentence might lead one to discount gator bait as cheap trash.However, when the main characters in the film are cheap trash, it simply gives it an authenticity rarely seen in todays cinema regardless of their budget.Good storytelling is what distinguishes a good film from the episodic messes passing for film nowadays.Gator bait has good storytelling, its sparse script keeps up perfectly with the action.The music is also simply exceptional and supports the visuals perfectly.There are a few scenes which obviously could have used more production and rehearsal time. However the cinematography as a whole depicts the beauty and danger of the swamp in an up close which is naturally unrehearsed.A movie for the whole family really.But don't take my word for it, ask billy bob!

reviewText: Okay, where do I begin? I was walking through my local Hollywood video, when I noticed this movie in the 10 for $10 VHS bin. It looked so raunchy that my fiancé and I simply had to buy it (it was either that or The King's Whore). We interpreted it as "soft-core porn" before our viewing of the movie, but now, we've done a complete 180.It wasn't classifiable as "soft-core porn," because porn has better dialogue, better acting,and superior special effects. Not to mention better music. Such artistic geniuses in this film's screenplay include Desiree's frequent use of the phrase, "Ye-hawwwwwwww!!!!!", and my favorite line, "I be back in two, three, day." Let's not forget the incredible death of Billy, when he got shot and made that sound like a twenty-year old bloodhound crapping out peach pits. Then, of course, Leroy's death was even better. He got shot in the chest and made a sound like a ninety-year old gargling beer.How about the spectacular stunt coordinator, who was so proud of his work, that he left his name out of the credits, and the husband/wife director/writer/producer team. You know that they did it all because no one else would touch it with a ten-foot pole.Let's elaborate more on the Oscar-winning performance of Claudia Jennings, may she rest in peace after the acting sin she committed in this film. This former playboy playmate said less than twenty words in the entire film, and disappointed men everywhere when she failed to get naked in the first five minutes. If it weren't for the potato sack blowing in the wind, most of them would have given up. We did, of course, get to see plenty of Janit Baldwin's thirteen-lookin' year old self as she bathed in the "clean" swamp waters. I wouldn't be surprised if the FBI came knocking on my door and arrested me for viewing child pornography.Then, if the Louisiana Cajun playmate ain't enough for you, let's add in who we called "The perv." In the first ten minutes of the film he was trying to rape some girl in a white dress while she was hanging up the laundry in the middle of the lawn, when his daddy came out and told him to get his hands off his sister. Wow, I wish my family was that f***ed up.Let's summarize. Blowing sacks, incest and crapping peach pits in Cajun country make this one hell of a family film. I hear Disney is even making an animated version

reviewText: I admit, I am no big fan on DVD-Rs. But some I do have look really good and come from legit studios (Warner, Universal, Columbia, MGM/Fox) and even though this version of GATOR BAIT is a DVD-R from a little known company, they did justice for this long anticipated DVD debut. Don't be fooled by the cheap/cheesy cover. What is on the disc is what counts! The print is very clean and clear (the only blemish are the reel changes (cigarette burns in upper right) since this is taken from a film print) and its in its original full frame format. Does not need to be widescreen, works fine as is. Looks as if the two directors had a hand in this release because there is a cool interview with the two of them that I really liked. But we buy this for Claudia Jennings! And I have been waiting years for this to come out on DVD and replace the crappy unwatchable VHS videotape version. This is probably the best print of this little drive-in classic as we are going to get. And I am one picky viewer! Always demanding widescreen with full blown surround sound. But this title doesn't need all the tricks that we come to expect. This movie is good as is.So don't be put off by it being a DVD-R and grab you a copy if you are a Claudia Jennings fan like me. Don't be scared it will look crappy, because its not. I was surprised how decent the image is!Now if only TRUCK STOP WOMEN get a decent release (and widescreen in its Techniscope aspect ratio) we Claudia fans will be all set.
summary: Don't believe the negative! This DVD-R looks really good for us Claudia Jennings fans.

reviewText: I collect dvds as a hobbie and actually bought Gatorbait 1 and 2 on dvd+r a few years before Amazon ever had them for sale. I purchased them from someone off ioffer.com and knew they were recorded onto dvd+r off an old vhs, because they hadn't been released to regular dvd yet.. The quality isn't the greatest. I ordered them off Amazon thinking they had finally been released on regular dvd.. A dream come true.. But, after I received my copies from Amazon and opened them it was really no different than what I already had.. I am sorry.. But, I know a boot leg dvd when I see one. Been collecting dvds for years and have bought quite a few recorded off television, or because they were out of print, or had never been released on regular dvd ect. Had a few that had a sticker label on them.. If this was actually released legally then it wouldn't have a cheap sticker on the cover on the dvd. I contacted Amazon immediately and let them know why I was sending them back.. Yeah, even Warner Bros. recently started making their movies on dvd+r but, they are genuine dvds.. "The Warner Archive collection" Not with a cheesy sticker.. But, a real dvd. Someone is just illegally trying to sale these out of print movies.. If they are legit then they seriously need to upgrade their dvds to where they adleast have actual labeling like a real dvd.. Still waiting for them to be released on regular dvd.. I'll just keep the dvd+r I first bought til then.. :PI gave 5 stars simply because I love these movies..
summary: Is this a boot leg dvd or what?

reviewText: Of all the films that the late Claudia Jennings made in the 70s, Gator Bait is the trashiest. It's about a gorgeous Cajun alligator poacher named Desire(Jennings), and her quest for vengeance on the redneck scum, who killed her younger sister.Desire lives in a backwoods swamp area, presumably in Louisiana or thereabouts. She poaches alligators as a living, and takes care of her two younger siblings. The three are orphans, with no other family to depend on for sustenance.One day when Desire is out poaching 'gators, she's ambushed by the local Sheriff's son, and his accomplice. The two attempt to rape Desire, and so she leads them on a merry boat chase through the swamp. They corner Desire, and she throws snakes that she caught into their boat. This allows Desire to escape their clutches. But the Sheriff's son accidentally kills his companion with a shotgun, when trying to shoot at the snakes in their boat.The Sheriff's son blames Desire for the killing of his companion. So then his father, along with the father of the dead guy, launch an all-out hunt for Desire in the swamp. Along the way, another of the rednecks hunting for Desire, goes to her cabin to look for her. Desire's little sister is there, and she's brutally murdered by the redneck. From then on, Desire becomes the hunter rather than the hunted, as she's determined to make the rednecks pay for killing her sister.Claudia Jennings is her usual voluptuous self in this film. Her hair and and make-up though, are too perfect for her role as a swamp-dwelling alligator poacher. Claudia did have the grace and athleticism, to handle the physically demanding role of Desire. The other actors, except for Janit Baldwin as Desire's sister, are dull and lifeless in their roles. The scenery in this film is decent, and realistically conveys the oppressive atmosphere, of a backwoods swamp.Gator Bait is a cult drive-in classic, no doubt due mainly to Claudia Jennings being in the starring role. Overall, this movie comes off as being ham-fisted and brutal, in its portrayal of the vicious redneck characters. For Claudia Jennings fans, the film is worth watching. But otherwise, Gator Bait has no other redeeming qualities about it at all.

reviewText: Desiree (Claudia Jennings) lives in the swamp with her younger brother, sister, and a  bad French accent applied to broken English. The law messes with her and she goes Rambette on them. However my memory seems to recall nude scenes that were deleted from this director's edition, especially those involving co-star Janit Baldwin. If I had to do again, I would go with the VHS.Parental Guide: No f-bombs. rape, nudity (Janit Baldwin, Claudia Jennings)

reviewText: Well this sought after "hick flick" is finally on a legal DVD. This is one of those movies that's been impossible to find since the rental places cleared their early 80's VHS tapes off the shelves. It's one of those staples of early 80's late night cable some people remember... and seeing Claudia Jennings is always a good thing!If you want an actual movie review, look elsewhere. But I figured someone should tell you what you're getting on the newly released DVD.The DVD is released independently by the film's producers. The outer packaging looks like photoshop 101... from 1999, making it look like a $3.99 porn DVD. The movie print is good for an old drive-in flick. The picture is enhanced for 16 x 9 but definitely isn't a real widescreen presentation. Of course no one's watching this for cinematography study, but these kinds of things can be distracting to movie fans.Extras include Spanish audio and a short "making of."There's also "where are they now" segments on the makers of the film, the Sebastians. The wife uses hers to talk about her greyhound rescue group. The husband uses his to testify about his "born again" story and plug his religious website. He mentions that the reason he's finally putting his films out on DVD (at what is basically the end of the format's lifespan) is in hopes his religious website will reach viewers. Well... at least now we know why this stuff's been unavailable for 20 something years.4 stars... mostly for being ably to cross this off my "will this ever show up on DVD" list and the fact that at $10 or less, they didn't price gouge.
Title: N/A
